</p>
<p>The idea is simple: if the client adds <code>?deep=1</code>, then the API should expose more
embedded objects. Use the asserter to say <code>assertResponsePropertyExists()</code>, pass
that the <code>$response</code> and the property we'll expect, which is <code>user</code>. Since this
will be an entire user object, check specifically for <code>user.username</code>:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="e172288684">
    <div class="meta">
        <div class="actions">
            <span class="fa fa-clipboard js-activate-clipboard" data-toggle="tooltip" title="Copy Code" data-placement="top"></span>
        </div>
