                    <td class="line-number line-number-displayed" data-line-number-displayed="127"></td>
            <td class="blob-code">        $context-&gt;setSerializeNull(<span class="hljs-keyword">true</span>);</td>
            </tr>
    <tr>
                    <td class="line-number line-number-displayed" data-line-number-displayed="128"></td>
            <td class="blob-code"></td>
            </tr>
    <tr>
                    <td class="line-number line-number-displayed" data-line-number-displayed="129"></td>
            <td class="blob-code">        <span class="hljs-keyword">return</span> <span class="hljs-keyword">$this</span>-&gt;container-&gt;get(<span class="hljs-string">'jms_serializer'</span>)</td>
            </tr>
    <tr>
                    <td class="line-number line-number-displayed" data-line-number-displayed="130"></td>
            <td class="blob-code">            -&gt;serialize($data, $format, $context);</td>
            </tr>
    <tr>
                    <td class="line-number line-number-displayed" data-line-number-displayed="131"></td>
            <td class="blob-code">    }</td>
            </tr>
    <tr>
                    <td class="line-number line-number-displayed" data-line-number-displayed="132"></td>
            <td class="blob-code">}</td>
            </tr>

        </tbody>
    </table>
</div>
</p>
<p>When we serialize, we create this <code>SerializationContext</code>, which holds a few options
for serialization. Honestly, there's not much you can control with this, but you <em>can</em>
set which <em>groups</em> you want to serialize.</p>
<p>First, get the <code>$request</code> object by fetching the <code>request_stack</code> service and adding
<code>getCurrentRequest()</code>. Next, create a new <code>$groups</code> variable and set it to only <code>Default</code>:
we <em>always</em> want to serialize the properties in this group:</p>
